{{Infobox person |name = Christine Boylan |image = |imagesize = |caption = |birth_name = Christine Ann Boylan |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1977|07|25}}<ref name=nytimeart>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/24/fashion/weddings/24Boylan.html?_r=0|title = Christine Boylan, Eric Heisserer|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=October 22, 2012|accessdate=October 9, 2012}}</ref> |birth_place = |years_active = 2007-present |occupation = Television writer, television producer |spouse = [[Eric Heisserer]] (m. 2010)}}
'''Christine Ann Boylan''' (born July 25, 1977<ref>{{cite web|title=United States Public Records, 1970-2009|url=https://familysearch.org/ark:/61903/1:1:KL3C-WCV|website=FamilySearch|accessdate=17 January 2017}}</ref>) is an American [[television writer]] and [[television producer|producer]]. She is known for her work on the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] [[Crime (genre)|crime]] series ''[[Castle (TV series)|Castle]]''.
==Life and career== Christine attended [[Hofstra University]].<ref name=nytimeart/> Since 2010, she has been married to screenwriter [[Eric Heisserer]].<ref name=nytimeart/> Her first job was on the planned [[NBC]] [[Apocalyptic and post-apocalyptic fiction|apocalyptic]] miniseries ''[[Day One (TV series)|Day One]]'', as an executive writer and story editor. The project ultimately never aired.<ref name=yahoocreds>{{cite web|url=https://tv.yahoo.com/christine-boylan/contributor/2383669|title=Christine Boylan CREDITS|work=Yahoo|accessdate=October 9, 2012}}</ref>
She was a writer and story editor on the [[TNT (U.S. TV network)|TNT]] drama ''[[Leverage (TV series)|Leverage]]'', from 2008-2010.<ref name=yahoocreds/> Her next position was at the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] medical drama ''[[Off the Map (TV series)|Off the Map]]'', as a writer and executive story editor. She contributed [[List of Off the Map episodes|two episodes]] during the show's only season.<ref name=yahoocreds/> In summer 2011, Boylan joined the [[Castle (season 4)|fourth season]] of the ABC crime series ''[[Castle (TV series)|Castle]]'', as a writer and co-producer. After the completion of the season she departed the show.<ref name=yahoocreds/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wetpaint.com/castle/articles/behind-the-scenes-of-castles-zombie-episode-stana-katic-poses-with-writer-christine-boylan-photo|title=Behind-the-Scenes of Castle's Zombie Episode: Stana Katic Poses With Writer Christine Boylan (PHOTO)|first=Lindsay|last=Dreyer|work=[[Wetpaint]]|date=April 5, 2012|accessdate=October 9, 2012}}</ref>
Boylan currently serves as writer and producer on the [[Once Upon a Time (season 2)|second season]] of the ABC [[Fantasy (genre)|fantasy]]/[[Mystery fiction|mystery]] ''[[Once Upon a Time (TV series)|Once Upon a Time]]''.<ref name=yahoocreds/> Episodes she has contributed to include: *"[[Tallahassee (Once Upon a Time)|Tallahassee]]" 2.06 <small>(co-written with consulting producer [[Jane Espenson]])</small> *"[[Tiny (Once Upon a Time)|Tiny]]" 2.13 <small>(co-written by producer [[Kalinda Vazquez]])</small> *"[[The Evil Queen (Once Upon a Time)|The Evil Queen]]" 2.20 <small>(co-written with consulting producer [[Jane Espenson]])</small> *''[[The Punisher (TV series)|The Punisher]]'', episode 1.06 <small>(writer)</small>
