{{Infobox Theatre |name = Las Vegas Little Theatre |image = |image_size = |caption = |address = 3844 Schiff Drive |city = [[Las Vegas, Nevada]] |coordinates = {{coord|36.171971|-115.144615|type:landmark|display=inline}} |owner = |capacity = 155 (Mainstage) |type = Local authority |opened = 1978 |othernames = |production = |website = lvlt.org }} '''Las Vegas Little Theater''' is a [[community theater]] in [[Las Vegas, Nevada]] that was founded in 1978 by Jack Bell and Jack Nickolson.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lvlt.org/about |title=About; Las Vegas Little Theatre |author= |date= |work= |publisher= |accessdate=2018-09-03}}</ref> Acting classes are available.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sagactor.blogspot.com/2009/11/las-vegas-theaters-partial-list-and.html |title=Las Vegas Theaters (partial list and contact links) |author=Art Lynch |date= |work= |publisher= |accessdate=2010-05-26}}</ref> It is the oldest operating small theater in the valley.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.marriott.com/hotels/local-city-guide.mi?marshaCode=lasfs&cityId=48&guideType=entertainment |title=Visitor's Guide: Las Vegas |author= |date= |work= |publisher= |accessdate=2010-05-28}}</ref>
