[[File:Ghari Bridge.JPG|thumb|240px|New pedestrian bridge built in Pahlavi period, west of Qari bridge]]
'''Qari Bridge''' is a historic stone<ref>[http://news.farsfoundation.net/en/tourist/tourist-attraction/416-a-land-area-of-east-azerbaijan-history-.html farsfoundation.net]</ref> bridges in [[Tabriz]], [[Iran]], over the [[Quri River]]. It has been built during [[Qajar dynasty]], and is a part of [[Seghat-ol-eslam street]], connecting [[Bazaar of Tabriz]] to the northern districts of Tabriz, among them [[Sheshgelan]] and [[Davachi (Tabriz)|Davachi]]. During [[Pahlavi dynasty]], a smaller bridge was built for the pedestrians.

