 [[File:Le roi Milutin de serbie.jpg|thumb|Serbian king [[Stefan Milutin]] issued the ''St. Stephen Chrysobull'' in 1314–16.]]
The '''St. Stephen Chrysobull''' ({{lang-sr|Светостефански хрисовуљ/Svetostefanski hrisovulj}}) or '''Banjska Chrysobull''' (Бањска хрисовуља/Banjska hrisovulja) was a [[Golden bull|chrysobull]], [[charter]], issued in 1314–16{{Cref2|a}} by Serbian king [[Stefan Milutin]] (r. 1282–1321). It was held at the [[Banjska monastery]] founded by Milutin. It is currently (as of 2004) held at the Topkapi library in [[Istanbul]].<ref name="Menković2004">{{cite book|author=Mirjana Menković|title=Kosovo i Metohija u svetlu etnologije: zbornik radova|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jYsMAQAAMAAJ|year=2004|publisher=Етнографски музеј у Београду|p=209}}</ref>
