[[File:Teatreprincipaldemao.jpg|thumb|]] [[File:A night at the Opera IV.jpg|thumb|Sala del Teatro Principal de Mahón]]
'''Teatre Principal de Maó''' ([[Catalan language|Catalan]]) or '''Teatro Principal de Mahón''' ([[Spanish language|Spanish]]) is an [[opera house]] located in the Spanish city of [[Mahón]], the capital of the island of [[Menorca]].
''The Principal'', as is known colloquially, is one of the oldest [[opera]] houses in [[Spain]]. It was built in 1829, to a design by Giovanni Palagi, according to the Italian standards of 18th century opera, and opened on 15 December 1829. Every year, ''The Principal'' hosts ''Opera Week'', an event where important opera figures who sing the ''[[bel canto]]'' repertoire perform. The theatre is also an important focus of [[Menorca]]n culture. ==References== {{reflist}} == External links == *[http://www.teatremao.com/main.php?lang=en Official website of the theatre] (In English)
